The chunk is part of the DirectNotify class, which manages multiple notify categories using a dictionary of Notifiers. The two methods in the chunk are used to get information about these categories: `getCategories()` returns a list of all category names, while `getCategory(categoryName)` retrieves the specific Notifier instance associated with the given category name or returns None if it doesn't exist.

#getters and setters
    def getCategories(self) -> list[str]:
        """
        Return list of category dictionary keys
        """
        return list(self.__categories.keys())

    def getCategory(self, categoryName: str) -> Notifier.Notifier | None:
        """getCategory(self, string)
        Return the category with given name if present, None otherwise
        """
        return self.__categories.get(categoryName, None)
